Orecchiette Pasta with Chicken Sausage and Broccoli

14 oz package chicken italian sausage, casing removed
12 oz uncooked pasta (or brown rice)
6 1/2 c fresh broccoli florets, no stems (16oz)
5 cloves garlic, smashed and chopped
1/4 c grated pecorino romano or parmesan cheese
2 tbsp olive oil
kosher salt and fresh cracked pepper

Bring a large pot of salted water to boil. Meanwhile, heat a large nonstick skillet and brown the sausage over medium high heat, breaking it up as it cooks with a wooden spoon until browned, 5-7 min; remove from heat. When the water boils, add the pasta and bring it back to a boil; when the water is boiling add broccoli and cook according to pasta instructions for al dente. When pasta is almost done cooking, reserve about 1 c of the water and set aside. Drain pasta and broccoli. Return the pot to the stove and set heat to high; add 1 tbsp olive oil, when hot add garlic. Cook until golden, ~1 min, reduve flame to low and add pasta back to the pot with the sausage. Mix well, add remaining oil, grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste mixing well and smashing any large piece of broccoli to break up. Add 1/2 c of reserved pasta water and mixx well, adding more if needed. Serve with additional grated cheese if desired.



Nutrition:
serving size 1 1/2 c
calories: 284
fat: 9g
carb: 37g
fiber: 4g
protein: 17g
sugar: 2g
sodium: 321mg
cholesterol: 2mg
